# Chapter 17 — The Final Arbiter

*The top floor is where the music stops. There are no more spreadsheets to hide behind, no more 'documentation' to use as a shield. There is only the CEO, the Auditor, and the weight of your own shadows.*

---

The CEO’s office was not an aquarium. It was a fortress. 

The walls were lined with physical books—leather-bound volumes on philosophy and warfare—and the view of the city was so panoramic it felt like looking at a map. Gabriel Soriano sat behind a desk made of ancient oak, his hands steepled. 

Beside him, Isabel Reyes stood like a statue carved out of corporate policy.

```
╔══════════════════════════════════════════╗
║               BOSS ENCOUNTER             ║
║                                          ║
║  Name: GABRIEL SORIANO (THE ARBITER)     ║
║  Rank: SSS (CEO)                         ║
║  Status: [ JUDICIAL ]                    ║
║                                          ║
║  Special Attack: 'The Termination Pen'   ║
║  (One signature ends your reality)       ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════╝
```

Juan and Cynthia stood in the center of the room. Juan’s STAMINA was at a lethargic 3%. He could barely keep his head up, but the System was forcing his spine to stay straight.

"Sit," Gabriel said. 

They sat. 

Gabriel looked at Juan for a long time. His eyes weren't angry. They were curious, which was much more dangerous. 

"Ms. Reyes has just finished a very interesting audit," Gabriel began. "It seems that Project Aethelgard, our most secure internal system, has a vulnerability. A vulnerability that was reported to me anonymously three nights ago."

He leaned forward, sliding a tablet across the desk. It showed the bug report that Juan had sent.

"This report," Gabriel continued, "is written in a style that I haven't seen in ten years. A style that belonged to a man named Rodel Magsino. A man who, according to our records, resigned in a state of mental collapse two weeks ago."

Isabel stepped forward, her tablet glowing. "I’ve cross-referenced the server logs, Gabriel. The report was sent from an 11th-floor terminal. A terminal assigned to Juan dela Cruz."

```
║  ALERT: DETECTION METER: 100% [||||||||||] ║
║  Status: [ EXPOSED ]                     ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════╝
```

The room went deathly silent. Juan felt the shadows of Rodel and Cynthia tighten around his ankles, ready to surge if he gave the command. But he knew that if he 'Raised' them here, he wouldn't just be fired. He’d be erased.

"I sent the report, sir," Juan said, his voice a whisper.

"Why?" Gabriel asked. "Why not go to your manager? Why not go to Aldrich Santos?"

"Because Aldrich Santos was the one who created the vulnerability, sir. He was using Aethelgard to hide the four million pesos he diverted during the Skyfall migration."

Isabel’s eyes widened. "That... that wasn't in the audit report."

"It was in the logs," Juan said, looking at her. "The unedited ones. The ones that only a System Worker could find."

Gabriel raised an eyebrow. "A 'System Worker'? Is that what you call yourself, Juan?"

Juan didn't answer. He couldn't explain the blue windows or the shadows. But he didn't have to. The CEO was already looking at the evidence.

"Aldrich Santos has already been 'relieved' of his duties," Gabriel said, his voice cold. "The evidence provided in the anonymous report was... undeniable. But that leaves the question of you, Mr. Dela Cruz."

He stood up and walked to the window, looking out over the city he owned.

"You’ve successfully implemented Phase 1 of Project Phoenix. The client is ecstatic. You’ve exposed a major corruption within my own executive floor. And you’ve managed to do all of this while being a Rank-F associate with no formal training in forensic auditing."

He turned back to Juan. 

"Ms. Reyes thinks you’re an anomaly. A bug in the system that needs to be deleted before it spreads. But I see something else."

Gabriel picked up his 'Termination Pen'. But he didn't sign a termination form. He signed a new Personnel Action notice.

```
╔══════════════════════════════════════════╗
║               DUNGEON CLEAR!             ║
║                                          ║
║  - Rank: D → C                           ║
║  - Status: [ CHOSEN BY THE ARBITER ]     ║
║  - Reward: [ IMMUNITY ] (30 Days)        ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════╝
```

"You're a Rank-C Technical Manager now, Juan. You report directly to me for Project Phoenix. Ms. Reyes will continue her audit, but she will do it as your 'Operational Consultant'. You will work together to ensure that no more 'anomalies' occur."

Isabel Reyes looked like she had just been told she had to work with a ghost. But she didn't argue. She simply nodded. 

"Understood, Gabriel."

Juan stood up, his legs feeling like they were finally going to give out. 

"Thank you, sir."

"Don't thank me, Juan," Gabriel said, his eyes meeting Juan’s one last time. "I don't believe in anomalies. I believe in results. Just make sure the Phoenix doesn't burn my building down."

Juan and Cynthia walked out of the office. 

As the elevator doors closed, Cynthia let out a breath that was half-laugh, half-sob. "Rank C. Directly reporting to the CEO. Juan, do you have any idea what you’ve just done?"

"I documented a bug, Cynthia," Juan said, leaning against the wall as his STAMINA hit 0%. "And then I Raising the solution."

He closed his eyes. 

The Phoenix had landed. But the shadows were now the ones holding the pen.

